        "latitude": null,
        "longitude": null,
        "type": "institute",
        "description": "Amani Research institute is a research institute located at Amani, in the Muheza District, on the Western Usambara Mountains of the northeastern region in present-day Tanzania. The mountains form part of the Eastern Arc Mountains, which stretch from Kenya through Tanzania, and are covered by tropical cloud forests that have endured a long period of unique evolutionary endemism.\nFounded during colonial rule in German East Africa in 1902 as research institute, it gained a strong reputation for botanical and agricultural research, as well as for the investigation of tropical diseases and the production of medical products."
    },
